post_text:
Join us Thursday, June 6, 2019 for our annual Focus On Life - Resource Fair for Addiction & Recovery at Focus Learning Academy East, 4480 Refugee Road. The event will be held from 11am until 3pm, rain or shine and is free to attend. Focus On Life provides education, resources, and recovery information to our Central Ohio community to assist individuals that are impacted by addiction. Our community partners this year include:

Nationwide Children’s Hospital
Franklin County Children’s Services
ADAMH
National Youth Advocate Program
Lower Lights Christian Health Center
Mid-Ohio Psychological Services, Inc.
Heartland High School (SUD Recovery Program)
Columbus Urban League
Southeast, Inc.
Southside Substance Solutions
Columbus Public Health (Alcohol & Drug Services)
Sun Behavioral Health
LSS Faith Mission
Huckleberry House
Youth to Youth International
North Community Counseling Centers
National Youth Advocate Program

post_text: Young mothers from around Central Ohio gathered at Focus East today for our 5th Annual Community Baby Shower with WHEP. The largest, and by far our best turnout since the start of the program. These mothers enjoyed an educational program for child care, as well as a generous supply of free diapers, formula, wipes, clothes and more. Thanks to all who attended this year's event!

Women's Health Education Program is with Mia Neil and 2 others.
May 21, 2018 at 7:47 PM ·

WHEP’s 4th Annual Community Baby Shower served 70 WIC-eligible Columbus Moms and their Children at Focus Schools in Celebration of Mother’s Day!! 💜

We distributed 2000+ baby items, 4000+ diapers while helping connect moms with community resources: St. Stephen's Community House, BC4Teens of Nationwide Children's Hospital, Molina Healthcare, Columbus Public Health, College & High School Aspiring Mother's Partnership for Success Program and The Center for Healthy Families 💜

Thank you to Focus Learning Academy, Columbus Diaper Coalition, Molina Healthcare and all our volunteers and community donors & supporters (especially Trinity Catholic School, NBC4 & Sunny Street Café) 💜
